%N A005792 Positive numbers that are the sum of 2 squares or 3 times a square.
%C A005792 Equivalently, numbers of the form k^2, k^2+m^2, or 3*k^2, where k >= 1, m >= 1.
%C A005792 Theorem (Golomb; Snover et al.): A triangle can be partitioned into n pairwise congruent triangles iff n is of the form k^2, k^2+m^2, or 3*k^2.
